OL,1,D]S737{kkkc5FBacklash after Bank boss   
OL,2,D]S555{jjj25Fsays don't ask for big pay 
OL,3,D]Suuu{rrzq5Frise                       
OL,4,T#######################################
OL,5, Unions have reacted with fury after the
OL,6, Bank of England boss urged workers not 
OL,7, to ask for big pay rises, to help stop 
OL,8, prices rising out of control.          
OL,10,FAndrew Bailey told the BBC wage rises  
OL,11,Fneeded to be moderate with firms       
OL,12,Fshowing "restraint" in pay talks.      
OL,14,FWhen asked whether the Bank was asking 
OL,15,Fworkers not to demand big pay rises, Mr
OL,16,FBailey, said: "Broadly, yes."          
OL,18,FDowning Street and the Treasury        
OL,19,Fdistanced themselves from Mr Bailey's  
OL,20,Fcomments.                              
